# Chrome Web Store Publishing Checklist

## Pre-Publication Checklist

- [ ] Manifest.json is valid (Manifest version 3)
- [ ] Extension icon/screenshot prepared (1280x800 minimum)
- [ ] Privacy policy created
- [ ] Extension description is clear and accurate
- [ ] All assets loaded locally (no external dependencies)
- [ ] Tested on multiple websites
- [ ] No console errors in content script

## Required for Chrome Web Store

1. **Developer Account**: Create a Chrome Web Store developer account
2. **Payment**: Pay the $5 registration fee
3. **Assets**:
   - Extension icon (128x128 px)
   - Screenshot (1280x800 px or 640x400 px)
   - Promotional image (440x280 px) - optional
4. **Listing Details**:
   - Short description (12 characters)
   - Full description
   - Category selection
   - Language selection

## Steps to Publish

1. Go to [Chrome Web Store Developer Dashboard](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/devconsole)
2. Click "New Item"
3. Upload the extension ZIP file
4. Fill in all required information
5. Upload promotional assets
6. Review and submit for approval
7. Wait for Google's review (usually 1-3 days)

## Packaging for Upload

To create a ZIP file for upload:
1. Right-click on the `chrome-extension` folder
2. Select "Send to" > "Compressed (zipped) folder"
3. This creates a ZIP ready for the Chrome Web Store
